To build the extension do the following:

Download the following Crypto-JS library files from http://code.google.com/p/crypto-js/downloads/list
    - 2.0.0-crypto.js
    - 2.0.0-md5.js
Place the files under chrome/content

Run make

An xpi file should appear in the root directory.

To install the extension:

Drag the xpi file to Firefox window.
Follow instructions.

The extension is known to work on some Firefox 4 beta versions.
